      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GALBA STACEY (1) is a quick dog who thrives over the short dashes. Finished second latest over 342m at Angle Park (19.54) in a Grade 5. Has an impeccable record here at this journey. Yet to miss the placings from three starts out of this box. Can go on with it. SAINT BREE (2) was sent out long odds last time but rocketed out of the boxes with a fast early sectional and gave a sight before being swallowed up late, finishing a 4.5 lengths third (17.81) over 305m at this track. Expected to feature. TRIAL KING (8) is worth forgiving last start after finishing seventh (30.28) from Box 2 at this track over 512m. Has never missed the frame from five starts from this draw, including three wins. Key runner on best form. REVITALISE (7) looks an each-way chance.",
